<font color="#FF0000">TO JOHN ON VISITING THE WALL</font><br>
<tt>Sun Jun 29 23:55:17 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
John,<br>
     Visited the wall with attendees of the Vietnam Helicopter CrewMembers Association on the 19th.  We had about 3 dozen guys who had never been there before.  Several became a bit teary, but that was to be expected and nothing to be ashamed of.  The rest of us made sure we were available if needed for moral support.<br><br>
     When you get to the point that you want to go; I suggest that you find another vet, preferrably someone who's been there, to go with you.  Having your family along may or may not be a good idea.  My boss almost scared his kids by breaking out in tears.  They had never seen him cry before. Other vets have testified to being grateful for their wife's emotional support on their first visit.  Your call.<br><br>
     If you can't get anybody; I would be willing to catch AMTRAK down from Philly and meet you in DC with at least 10 days notice; so I can arrange to be on leave.<br><br>
                                  Welcome aboard the site,<br>
                                  Gerry<br>
      
<p><code>-- gerald_ney@icpphil.navy.mil  (Gerald Ney, &quot;professor&quot;, 7/68-7/69) </code><p>


